exam1.question: Which of the following statements about fixed mindset is true?
exam1.option1: When adopting a fixed mindset, you are more likely to use the word “yet” when you talk about what you can’t do, or what you don’t know.
exam1.option2: Students who adopted a fixed mindset were more likely to see their failures as indicators that they were not smart, rather than as opportunities to learn.
exam1.option3: If someone is adopting a fixed mindset, their beliefs about the nature of intelligence are more accurate than someone adopting a growth mindset.
exam1.option4: Students who were trained to have a fixed mindset performed better in mathematics than students who were trained to have a growth mindset.
exam1.Correctanswer: Students who adopted a fixed mindset were more likely to see their failures as indicators that they were not smart, rather than as opportunities to learn.

exam1.question: Which factor was the highest predictor of success for Spelling Bee (spelling competition) contestants?
What is growth mindset?
exam1.option1: Holding a belief that one’s character, intelligence, and/or creative ability are carved in stone and can’t change in any meaningful way.
exam1.option2: Holding a belief that success is a result of one’s innate intelligence and/or talents.
exam1.option3: Holding a belief that one’s intelligence and abilities can grow through dedication and hard work.
exam1.option4: Holding a belief that your failure means that you lack what it takes to be successful.
exam1.Correctanswer: Holding a belief that one’s intelligence and abilities can grow through dedication and hard work.
